comments: Sengun (HOU) absorbs the contact initiated by Hart (NYK) while he is airborne and about to release the pass.
Green (HOU) legally contests Burks's (NYK) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Sengun (HOU) extends his off-arm into Achiuwa (NYK) to create space.
Brunson (NYK) keeps his right hand on top of the ball as he takes his dribble.

Sengun (HOU) contests the jump shot attempt by Burks (NYK) and after he releases the ball, makes slight contact with his head.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Achuwa (NYK) maintains a legal defensive position in the post against Sengun (HOU).
Brooks (HOU) briefly touches Brunson's (NYK) back as he enters his shooting motion and the contact is marginal.
Bogdanovic (NYK) extends both hands forward and initiates contact with Thompson (HOU) during the drive, affecting his SQBR.
Hart (NYK) makes contact with the ball and the ensuing contact with Sengun (HOU) is incidental.
Hart (NYK) reaches in and makes contact with the ball, jarring it loose from Sengun's (HOU) possession.  Sengun legally recovers the loose ball and starts his dribble.
Achiuwa (NYK) establishes his position and absorbs the contact during Sengun's (HOU) driving shot attempt.
After Sengun (HOU) releases the driving shot attempt, the ball gets stuck in the side of the rim. The game resumes with a jump ball at center circle.
Brooks (HOU) legally contests Brunson's (NYK) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Achiuwa (NYK) cleanly blocks Green's (HOU) driving shot attempt.
Brunson (NYK) legally contests Holiday's (HOU) shot. Holiday released his shot before contact with Brunson and is able to return to a normal floor position.
